%N A064849 Period of continued fraction for sqrt(3)*n.
%H A064849 Robert Israel, <a href="/A064849/b064849.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%e A064849 A040001 (cfrac for n=1) has period length 2, so a(1)=2. A040008 (cfrac for n=2) has period length 2, so a(2)=2. A040021 (cfrac for =3) has period length 2, so a(3)=2. - _R. J. Mathar_, Feb 10 2016
%p A064849 f:= proc(n) uses NumberTheory;
%p A064849    nops(Term(ContinuedFraction(sqrt(3)*n),periodic)[2])
%p A064849 end proc:
%p A064849 map(f, [$1..100]); # _Robert Israel_, Apr 14 2026
%t A064849 Table[Length[Last[ContinuedFraction[Sqrt[3] n]]], {n, 128}]
%Y A064849 Cf. A064848, A064850, A064851, A064860, A064862, A064863, A064864, A064887, A064897, A064912.
